timeline.bodyText:
Not sure about whether an established pattern exists for this kind of operation. In some other samples we do .addDoneLoadingListener() first, then call .loadAsync(). Again, I'm not too fussed which way it goes, but would be nice if it were consistent 😄 Maybe add something to the contribution guide as well, once this is decided?
Because we do things with async operations in this order (async call first, then add listener):
ListenableFuture<List<FeatureTableEditResult>> resultOfApplyEdits = serviceGeodatabase.applyEditsAsync();
resultOfApplyEdits.addDoneListener(() -> {

It might be best to do it the way you have here (loadAsync first, then add listener).
I think we could add this to the contribution guide, and perhaps even make an issue for technical debt to make this all consistent

